From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: debug <debug@debug.local>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2026 01:00:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] ath10k: core: add debug prints to register and
 register_work

Add dev_info prints to ath10k_core_register() and
ath10k_core_register_work() to trace whether the workqueue is
being scheduled and executed.

Signed-off-by: debug <debug@debug.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/core.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/core.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/core.c
index abcdef0..1234567 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/core.c
@@ -3510,6 +3510,8 @@
 	struct ath10k *ar = container_of(work, struct ath10k, register_work);
 	int status;
 
+	dev_info(ar->dev, ">>> ath10k_core_register_work ENTER\n");
+
 	/* peer stats are enabled by default */
 	set_bit(ATH10K_FLAG_PEER_STATS, &ar->dev_flags);
 
@@ -3584,6 +3586,7 @@
 {
 	ar->bus_param = *bus_params;
 
+	dev_info(ar->dev, ">>> ath10k_core_register: queueing work\n");
 	queue_work(ar->workqueue, &ar->register_work);
 
 	return 0;
